<taxonomicName id="4C0E95D9FFB3C0548238F969BBE9F95B" box="[1059,1158,1678,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB3C0548238F969BBE9F95B" box="[1059,1158,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="530">N. minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the ventral process of aedeagal shaft more strongly curved apically.
</paragraph>
